				<wikidot:authorName>Monteparnas</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2926286</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This seemed really weak at the start, and almost lost me. I'm so glad I read it all. This is a skip to be proud of, unnerving without being overtly dangerous, with characters well developed in a fast enough pace. The subtle hint of intimidation in the last line of the &quot;Agent's 'mother'&quot; was gold.</p> <p>Unfortunately, it is too late now. Tomorrow morning I'm calling my mother.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
